meanings: Chemical Formula H2N2S2. A chemical structure of a molecule includes the arrangement of atoms and the chemical bonds that hold the atoms together. The 1$l^{4},3$l^{4},2,4-dithiadiazete molecule contains of 2 Hydrogen atom(s), 2 Nitrogen atom(s) and 2 Sulfur atom(s) – a total of 6 atom(s).

Chemical Formula HN3S3. A chemical structure of a molecule includes the arrangement of atoms and the chemical bonds that hold the atoms together. The 1$l^{4},3$l^{4},5,2,4,6-trithiatriazine molecule contains of 1 Hydrogen atom(s), 3 Nitrogen atom(s) and 3 Sulfur atom(s) – a total of 7 atom(s).
